	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>Oct 4 1859</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear friend&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I have duly recd your<lb/> Letter of the <date>11th</date> ulto also the list of your debtors for<lb/> the subscription of the &#8220;Occident&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I send you enclosed sight Draft on<lb/> <persName>Drexel &#38; Co</persName> for &#36;65.20 for which I have paid<lb/> 2&#37; exchange making &#36;1.30&#162; which together amount<lb/> to &#36;66.50&#44; being the amount I have collected<lb/> for the subscription of the &#8220;Occident&#8221; as follows&#58;</p>
				<table rows="12" cols="3">
				<row>
				<cell><persName>M. Mayblum</persName></cell>
				<cell><placeName>San Francisco</placeName></cell>
				<cell>&#36;3.00</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>H. Neustadter</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>5.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>D. Stern</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>5.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>Samuel Marx</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>9.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>Hamburger Brothers</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>10.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>L. Tichner</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>6.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>Scholle Bros</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>7.50</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>Lazard Freres</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>9.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>H. W. Stein</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>3.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>Jules Cerf</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220;</cell>
				<cell>6.&#8212;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>J. A. Brunner</persName></cell>
				<cell>&#8220; 1 year adv.</cell>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">3.&#8212;</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>&#40;making the above mentioned sum&#41;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell>&#36;66.50</cell>
				</row>
				</table>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will perceive that the most of mentioned<lb/> payments are not in full&#44; as I have followed<lb/> out your requests &#38; have compromised with</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>all those who complained that they did not<lb/> receive the &#8220;Occidents&#8221; regularly&#44; that they never<lb/> ordered them&#44; that they gave notice for a<lb/> discontinuation &#38;c &#38;c.  &#38; I have deemed it<lb/> to be your benefit to comply with your request<lb/> &#38; took all I could get from the parties.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You have <persName>Mr Mayblum</persName> down for 2 years&#59;<lb/> he says that he recd the &#8220;Occident&#8221; in the capacity<lb/> of <placeName>South Carolina</placeName> of Post Master &#38; as such did<lb/> not think himself liable for any subscription &#38;c<lb/> therefore I have compromised it for &#36;3.00</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#36;5.00 is all I could collect from <persName>H Neustadter</persName>&#59;<lb/> says that he did not wish the Occid for<lb/> some time&#59; he <hi rend="underline">wishes to stop his subscription</hi><lb/> The same remark is applicable to <persName>D. Stern</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Saml Hart</persName> wishes all the back<lb/> Nos since the weekly has been commenced</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Hamburger Bros</persName> think they cannot owe<lb/> you &#36;15.00&#44; still if you were sure they will<lb/> pay the Balance of &#36;5.00</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#36;7.50 was the most I could draw from <persName>Scholle<lb/> Bros</persName>&#59; they wish the &#8220;Occident&#8221; no more.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>H. W. Stern</persName> makes the reason for paying<lb/> less&#44; not receiving it &#38; <add>&#63;</add>&#59; he also wishes to<lb/> discontinue his subscription</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr S. T. Meyer</persName>&#44; whom you have on the<lb/> list resides now at <placeName>New York</placeName>&#59; <persName>Mr Aaron<lb/> Jacobs</persName> there can tell you where he can be<lb/> found.  <persName>Jules Cerf</persName> makes also the excuse</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>not having subscribed &#38; <add>&#63;</add> he wishes to dis&#45;<lb/>&#45;continue his subscription&#44; you will observe<lb/> that I also settled with him.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Since you gave me authority to settle<lb/> with the parties who made excuses &#38; complaints<lb/> to escape payments&#44; I have used it&#44; &#38;<lb/> with my most active endeavors in your<lb/> behalf have I worked to make these collections&#44;<lb/> &#38; I trust you will approve of my work.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I would beg leave to suggest to you to<lb/> stop always the subscription when desired&#44;<lb/> as you cannot afford to supply people<lb/> with papers without their wishes &#38; payments.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please do not forget to acknowledge<lb/> in your next issue all the various<lb/> payments as collected&#59; as I have not given<lb/> any receipts&#44; save in a single instance.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please accept the following new<lb/> subscribers I got&#58; <persName><hi rend="underline">Lewis Cohn</hi></persName>&#44; <placeName>San Francisco</placeName><lb/> <persName>J. A. <hi rend="underline">Bruner</hi></persName>&#44; <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>&#44; &#40;the latter<lb/> gentleman has paid one year&#39;s subscription<lb/> in advance&#44; which you will observe amongst<lb/> the list of collections&#41; <persName><hi rend="underline">Regensburger</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">&#38; Stern</hi></persName> <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>&#44; whose subscription<lb/> is in place of <persName>D Stern</persName> &#40;discontinued&#41;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Alexander Mayer</persName> who arrived<lb/> here in safety from <placeName>Phil</placeName> requests me to<lb/> state that he has sold all the bibles save<lb/> one.  <persName>Mr Jacob Bloomingdale</persName> whom</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>you have on the list lives now in<lb/> <placeName>Germany</placeName> think <placeName>Frankfort</placeName>.  I see that you have<lb/> <persName>Haas</persName> &#38; <persName>Rosenfeld</persName> on the list for &#36;15.00&#44; which<lb/> is doubtful that I will be able to collect<lb/> as on their last payment they requested<lb/> a discontinuance&#44; of which I wrote you<lb/> at the time.  <persName>Raphael Schoyer</persName> is<lb/> not in the city&#44; he left for <placeName>Japan</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>S. Fleishhacker</persName> resides at <placeName>Placerville</placeName><lb/> &#38; I hope you will not send him<lb/> the &#8220;Occident&#8221; as you can never ex&#45;<lb/>&#45;pect a cent from him&#44; being too fond<lb/> of whiskey &#38; rum.  <persName>Hess</persName> lives in <placeName>N York</placeName>.<lb/>  where <persName>Cha&#45;Simon</persName> is I cannot tell&#44;<lb/> you better therefore discontinue sending<lb/> the &#8220;Occid&#8221; to him.  From <persName>F. M.<lb/> Reinhart</persName> I cannot collect anything&#59; he<lb/> lives here now &#38; am well acquainted<lb/> with him.  <persName>Aaron Rosenheim</persName> does not<lb/> live anymore at <placeName>Nevada</placeName>&#44; he resides<lb/> here now&#59; I think his Brother lives there<lb/> yet.  You are wrong in believing <del>then</del><lb/> <persName>Aaron Rosenheim</persName> rich.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have made those collections<lb/> all myself&#59; time did not allow me<lb/> to call on every one as yet&#44; but shall<lb/> do so as soon as I shall have some</p>
		</body>
	</text>
